PRIMITIVE ID.long-description: Must consist of printable ASCII characters (like ST) and contain a value present in the associated table, which must not be user-defined.

PRIMITIVE IS.long-description: Must consist of printable ASCII characters (like ST) and contain a value present in the associated table, which must be user-defined.

PRIMITIVE NM.long-description: Numeric data written in decimal, the allowable characters are the ASCII digits, the leading plus and minus sign, and a single decimal point.

PRIMITIVE SI.long-description: A non-negative integer in the form of an NM field. The uses of this data type are defined in the chapters defining the segments and messages in which it appears.

PRIMITIVE ST.long-description: Up to 199 printable ASCII characters in the ASCII range 0x20 (32) to 0x7E (126) except the defined delimiter characters.
